<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-45-0381 </DOCNO><TEXT>Today everyone has to be prepared to meet the challenges presented bynew legislative actions. The Savannah River Plant is also impacted bythis legislation as the exclusive nature of the Atomic Energy Act slowlyerodes. This paper discusses the management of three types of radioactivewaste from the production of defense nuclear materials and the impactsof major environmental legislation on the handling of these wastes. Thepaper briefly discusses the major environmental statutes, covers thestatutes impact on the technical processes and, finally, considers thenontechnical impact of the statutes.</TEXT></DOC>